OL,3,CConsumer confidence in economy 'at
OL,4,Clowest level since cost-of-living
OL,5,Cshock'
OL,7,FConfidence fell by seven points to
OL,8,Fminus 53 in April ` its lowest level
OL,9,Fsince December 2022 when the cost-of-
OL,10,Fliving crisis was at its height and
OL,11,Fthe inflation rate was above 10%.
OL,13,FWhen Which? asked respondents who
OL,14,Freported being pessimistic why they
OL,15,Ffelt so negatively about the future UK
OL,16,Feconomy, 67% said it was because of
OL,17,Fglobal events, while 63% cited changes
OL,18,Fin prices and 60% mentioned government
OL,19,Ftax changes.
