OL,5,Cshock'
OL,7,FThe proportion of renters missing rent
OL,8,Fpayments increased to 4.7% in the last
OL,9,Fmonth, suggesting many are still
OL,10,Fstruggling to make ends meet due to
OL,11,Fongoing cost-of-living pressures.
OL,13,FAn estimated 13 million households
OL,14,F(46%) made at least one adjustment to
OL,15,Fcover essential spending such as
OL,16,Futility bills, housing costs,
OL,17,Fgroceries, school supplies and
OL,18,Fmedicines in the last month, although
OL,19,Fthis was slightly lower than the 51%
OL,20,Fseen in March.
